  "prompt": "If you block someone on Instagram could they still see you in the followers list of an account that didn't block them and they already know?",
  "response": "If you block someone on Instagram, they won\u2019t be able to see your profile or your posts. However, your presence in the followers list of accounts that have not blocked them remains unchanged\u2014they can still see you listed as a follower of those accounts.\n\nBlocking someone on Instagram is mainly to prevent them from interacting with you directly, but it doesn\u2019t remove your visibility from lists or interactions that are not directly linked to your account. So, if they check the followers list of a mutual connection, they might still see your account there.",
